## TL;DR — Elongated Oval Diamond Ring in {{year}}

An elongated oval diamond ring is a ring built around an oval diamond with a length-to-width (L/W) ratio of 1.50 or higher — the point at which the stone transitions from the classic oval silhouette into a dramatically elongated one. The elongated oval delivers the most pronounced finger-lengthening effect of any brilliant-cut diamond, faces up larger than a classic oval of equal carat weight, and is the dominant engagement ring trend in {{year}}.

**The critical risk:** As L/W ratio increases past 1.50, bow-tie shadow intensifies. By 1.65, you are in high-probability bow-tie territory. The stone you buy must be evaluated on video — not from a static image or a GIA certificate.

**The best elongated oval solitaire:** [Classic Six-Prong at $1,000](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-six-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-item-203272?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (1,894 reviews) + a [2ct GIA G-VS2 elongated oval](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=2&Color=G&Clarity=VS2&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at [$17,480](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=2&Color=G&Clarity=VS2&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = **[$18,480 total](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Oval&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.

**Why six prongs for elongated ovals:** The pointed tips of an elongated oval are the most vulnerable points of the stone. The six-prong design places prongs at both tips, protecting the most fragile geometry. A four-prong setting leaves the tips exposed. See the [complete solitaire guide](/oval-diamond-solitaire-engagement-ring) for all options.

