### Bezel Settings — Underrated for High L/W Ratios

The bezel setting wraps a continuous metal rim around the entire perimeter of the stone. For elongated ovals, this is the strongest mechanical solution — the elongated tips are fully enclosed by metal rather than held by a single prong.

The tradeoff: a bezel setting reduces the apparent face-up size of the oval by 15–22% because the metal rim covers the outer edge of the stone. However, for buyers with L/W ratios of 1.60 or higher — where tip vulnerability is greatest — the bezel offers protection that no prong setting can match.

