The bezel's clean metal frame also visually emphasizes the elongated outline — particularly in yellow gold, where the warm band creates a clear visual contrast with the stone's outline. See the [oval diamond bezel setting guide](/oval-diamond-bezel-setting) for all options.

### Halo Settings — Maximum Apparent Size

A halo adds a ring of accent diamonds around the center stone's perimeter, increasing apparent face-up size by 20–30%. For elongated oval diamonds, a halo also extends the visual length of the ring north-to-south — amplifying the finger-lengthening effect beyond what the stone achieves alone.

The key consideration: at L/W 1.60+, a traditional circular halo will create a slightly mismatched perimeter around the elongated stone. An oval-shaped halo that mirrors the stone's elongated outline creates a more visually cohesive result. The [Falling Edge Pavé Halo](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/falling-edge-pave-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-by-james-allen-item-311115?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) uses an oval halo frame that works well with both classic and elongated center stones.

