## Large Oval Diamond Rings: 3ct and Above

For buyers in the large oval category (3ct+), the elongated outline becomes proportionally more important. A 3ct oval at 1.40 L/W can look blocky and wide — the sheer mass of the stone at standard proportions creates a wider stone that sits more like a round brilliant than the elongated elegant shape most oval buyers want.

At 3ct+, target L/W 1.50–1.60. This keeps the stone proportional to the finger — longer north-to-south without growing too wide east-west. The bow-tie audit is mandatory at 3ct+ in any L/W ratio above 1.50.

**The 3ct elongated oval price:** [3ct GIA G-VS2](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=3&Color=G&Clarity=VS2&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at [$36,883](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=3&Color=G&Clarity=VS2&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [Comfort Fit Six Prong at $1,240](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/comfort-fit-six-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-by-james-allen-item-316246?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = **[$38,123](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Oval&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** total.

