## Vintage Settings for Elongated Oval Diamond Rings

Vintage and Art Deco settings work with elongated ovals when the setting's filigree or milgrain detail runs parallel to the stone's elongated axis. Settings with heavy geometric ornamentation perpendicular to the stone's length can visually interrupt the elongation effect.

The [Art Deco Fleur-De-Lis Pavé by JA at $1,570](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/art-deco-inspired-fleur-de-lis-pave-vintage-style-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-315295?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (101 reviews) is the highest-reviewed vintage setting that works well with elongated ovals — its pavé detail follows the stone's contour without interrupting the north-south visual line. The [Hand-Engraved Micropavé at $2,315](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/hand-engraved-micropave-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-1-6-ct-tw-item-194236?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (87 reviews) pairs hand-engraving with micropavé for a deeply detailed Art Deco look that complements the elongated form.

